# Infrastructure Standards

## Terraform

- All GCP resources defined in Terraform — no manual console clicks
- Use variables for anything environment-specific
- State stored in GCS backend bucket
- Run `terraform plan` before every `terraform apply`
- Log every apply in `docs/run_log.md`

## Docker

- Multi-stage builds to minimize image size
- Pin base image versions (e.g., `python:3.12-slim`, not `python:latest`)
- Non-root user in production containers
- `.dockerignore` must exclude `node_modules`, `.env`, `__pycache__`, `.git`

## Google Cloud

- Project ID and region set via environment variables
- Cloud Run services must have health check endpoints
- All secrets in Secret Manager — mounted as env vars in Cloud Run
- Enable Cloud Logging and Cloud Trace on all services
